results.name: Permutation of natural numbers: a(n) = A269380(A250469(n)).
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
Index entries for sequences that are permutations of the natural numbers
example: For n=9 we first find what number is below 9 in square array A083221, which is 25, then we find what number is above 25 in square array A255127, which is 23, thus a(9) = 23.
xref: More recursed variant: A269357. Cf. also permutations A266645, A255407, A269171.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Mar 03 2016
